WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.940
Of course, the President doesn't personally borrow money.

00:00:01.960 --> 00:00:05.820
Really, the Department of the Treasury, that he oversees, issues debt on behalf of the US government,

00:00:05.820 --> 00:00:09.720
and fully explaining the process by which the government issues debt in the same department

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:11.800
that both prints new cash and collects taxes

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:14.400
quickly leads to questions about money's existential nature.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:16.760
So, for simplicity's sake, let's just ignore that for now.

